
1. Clone (pull code from GitHub to VS Code)


git clone https://github.com/username/repo.git
cd repo
code .

2. Create a Feature Branch

Always create a new branch (never work directly on `main`)


git checkout -b feature/my-feature-name


3. Add folders and Python files

Create manually in VS Code explorer or terminal


mkdir new_folder
touch new_folder/app.py

4. Add & commit changes

git add .
git commit -m "Added new folder and python files"

5. Push branch to GitHub


git push origin feature/my-feature-name

6. Create Pull Request (PR)

1. Go to GitHub repo in browser
2. Click “Compare & pull request”
3. Add description
4. Click Create Pull Request

7. Merge to main

Option A (GitHub UI):

1. Click "Merge pull request"
2. Confirm merge



Option B (locally):


git checkout main
git pull origin main
git merge feature/my-feature-name
git push origin main

8. Clean up (optional but good practice)

git branch -d feature/my-feature-name
# -D if you want to force delete without checking merged status
git push origin --delete feature/my-feature-name
git fetch --prune
